# Project Title: IoT Based Smart Shed Automation for Crop Protection

## Technical Stack:
- Arduino MEGA
- ESP32 Devkit
- Blynk IoT Cloud
- Motor Drivers
- DC Motors
- Temperature & Rain Drop Sensor
- C++

## Description:
Designed and implemented an Arduino Mega-based automation system to control shed mechanisms, 
utilizing DC motors for precise opening and closing actions in response to environmental triggers like high temperature and Raindrops.
Established seamless communication with the Blynk IoT cloud platform using ESP32 DevKit, 
facilitating real-time data transfer and remote monitoring of environmental conditions. 
This integration enables timely alerts and remote management of shed operations, enhancing crop protection and management efficiency.
